  "name": "RPlog_How_Much_is_Too_Much",
  "title": "The Breaking of Shael Edur",
  "summary": "Held in sensory-deprivation darkness as prisoner C-1125, the captured Republic informant Shael Edur is dragged before an ISB interrogator in a chamber dominated by a vat of corrosive liquid and rows of bound prisoners suspended above it. The coldly methodical agent presses her to reveal her true work for the New Republic, dismissing her claim to be a mere smuggler. To break her resolve, he drops a young boy into the acid vat, then prolongs the child's agony before killing him, threatening the rest of the captives. Overwhelmed with guilt and horror, Shael confesses that she is NRI, an informant reporting directly to the Chief of State. Satisfied, the agent spares the remaining prisoners, orders her fed and tended, and praises her compliance in the Emperor's name, leaving Shael to spiral into self-harm and despair as the slow, patient machinery of her psychological breaking continues.",
